			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It seems (oddly) to vary by zone.  Perhaps there's some boilerplate zone file that they use for development or else it depends on who's coding the zone.  Some places (seb, lguk, solro tower, PoV...) seem to have a zone-wide tick...everybody in the zone gets their dot reports and whatnot at the same time, and it's possible to sneak by mobs as you described.  Other places (ldon, i'm pretty sure every zone) they seem to be player-based, or at least things are updated client-side at different intervals...I don't trust this as informal testing (and moreso gut feeling) indicates that things are still happening at the same time for everybody, and clients are getting the information at different times.
<br />

<br />
Lately (constantly in the past few weeks, off-and-on for a few weeks before that, as if they're testing some new optimization) there's yet another layer of tomfoolery going on.  Songs (and all spells, though most non-bards haven't been as quick to pick up on it for the obvious reasons) aren't always &quot;landing&quot; when they normally would instantly as cast but sluggishly waiting until the tick to go into effect.  Neither lag nor client slowness seem to be an issue here, the server's just aren't recognizing that the *&amp;@!# song has landed when they normally would. :(</span></td>
